{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01KiVMCV8Gpgiv4Q98Sz5mLf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All four checks pass:\n- ruff check: passed\n- ruff format --check: passed (after one reformat)\n- pytest: 336 passed\n- mypy: clean\n\nTask 2.6.1 done. Added `_check_structural_sanity(lines, source_path)` to `bob_tools/planfile/parser.py` — a pre-parse scan that raises `PlanSyntaxError` listing every anomaly (duplicate H1 titles, multiple Bugs sections at any heading level, duplicate phase/stage ordinals) with 1-based line locators. It is invoked from `parse_plan` immediately after `splitlines()`, before any structural parsing, so the typed `Plan` never has to represent a corrupted document. Order of recognition matches mcloop (stage → bugs → H1) so `# Phase 1: ...` is not double-counted. Added 10 tests in a new `TestCheckStructuralSanity` class covering each anomaly individually, the H1/stage disambiguation, multi-error aggregation, source-path passthrough, and clean-plan no-op."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":116,"cache_read_input_tokens":103927,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":116},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"60d85b9b-07d2-4666-b129-0e41e9f14a76","uuid":"089a3373-dd48-42e2-b448-b549eda1e790"}
